oup commonly known as simply huron is a global management consulting company offering services to the healthcare higher education life sciences and commercial industries in fiscal year ending december   huron generated  million in annual revenue contents  history  recent acquisitions  myrounding  cloud  rittman mead india  studer group  sky analytics  threshold consulting inc  vonlay llc  frankel group  blue stone international  click commerce  revenue  financial restatement  recognition  references  external links historyedit huron was founded in may  in chicago illinois the company’s initial employees included former consultants from arthur andersen including  partners and  other professionals as of  huron had more than  employees in may  huron filed a registration statement with the securities and exchange commission sec relating to the initial public offering of its common stock huron consulting group inc the holding company became a public company trading common stock on the nasdaq global select market exchange under the ticker “hurn” in october  recent acquisitionsedit hsm on july   huron acquired healthcare services management inc hsm a healthcare information technology consultant whose clients include allscripts athenahealth cerner and epic systems adi strategies on may   huron acquired adi strategies inc an enterprise performance management and business intelligence firm that has been recognized as an oracle platinum partner myroundingedit on february   huron acquired myrounding a firm specializing in digital health solutions to improve patient care cloudedit on october   huron acquired cloud a firm specializing in complex salesforcecom implementations and related cloudbased applications rittman mead indiaedit on july   huron acquired the india affiliate of rittman mead consulting ltd rittman mead india a data and analytics consulting firm that specializes in the implementation of enterprise performance management and analytics systems studer groupedit on feb   huron acquired studer group a professional services firm that consults with healthcare providers on clinical outcomes and financial results sky analyticsedit on jan   huron acquired sky analytics a massachusettsbased provider of legal software for corporate law departments threshold consulting incedit on oct   huron acquired threshold consulting inc a consulting firm that provides customer relationship management consulting cloudbased software as a service applications business intelligence solutions and data warehousing vonlay llcedit on may   huron acquired vonlay llc a healthcare technology consulting firm specializing in clinical administrative and financial system implementation and optimization frankel groupedit on january   huron acquired the frankel group associates llc a life sciences consulting firm  blue stone internationaledit on september   huron acquired blue stone international llc a provider of oracle corporation professional services supporting enterprise performance management information management and business intelligence solutions under the terms of the agreement huron will acquire the assets of blue stone for  million in cash  click commerceedit huron acquired click commerce a supplier of softwarebased solutions and professional services to academic medical centers and research institutions terms of the acquisition were not disclosed revenueedit                       financial restatementedit on july   huron announced that the company would restate its financial statements for    and first quarter  that same day huron announced the resignation of its chairman of the board and ceo gary holdren cfo gary burge and that chief accounting officer wayne lipski would soon be departing the company also announced that james h roth a founder of the company would be hurons new ceo the following business day  august    huron’s shares dropped  percent to  the company had reported that shareholders of four huron business acquisitions acquired between  and  conditionally redistributed portions of their initial and future acquisitionrelated payments among themselves and to certain huron employees without hurons knowledge or permission the issue was initially identified by the chief accounting officercontroller wayne lipski on july   huron announced it has reached a final settlement with the us securities and exchange commission sec resolving the previously disclosed sec investigation into the company’s august  restatement of its financial statements for the years ended   and  and the first quarter of  the company agreed to the settlement without admitting or denying the sec’s findings recognitionedit huron was named one of forbes america’s best employers for  and  huron was named one of consulting magazine’s best firms to work for in      and  huron received consulting magazine’s excellence in social  community investment award in   and  consulting magazine named gordon mountford executive vice president huron healthcare as one of the top  most influential consultants in  consulting magazine named laura yaeger founding member and leader of huron consulting groups education and life sciences practice as one of the top  consultants in  consulting magazine named dr andrew ziskind managing director and clinical solutions leader huron healthcare as one of the top  most influential consultants in  consulting magazine named james h roth ceo and president as one of the top  most influential consultants in  and  the turnaround management association tma recognized huron as one of the winners of the  tma turnaround and transaction of the year awards huron financial was honored for its turnaround of bancroft bag inc huron healthcare was ranked in the top five of modern healthcare’s largest healthcare management consulting firms for the past  years huron was named a  and  top workplace by the oregonian huron was named a  and  top workplace by the chicago tribune hurons ecrt click and efacs were selected as readers choice top pr