diction looks to find earnings surprises by focusing on the most recent analyst revisions this is done because generally speaking if an analyst reevaluates their earnings estimate right before an earnings release it means that they have fresh information which could potentially be more accurate than what analysts thought about a company two or three months ago the crux of this approach is comparing the most accurate estimate to the zacks consensus estimate although the zacks rank is also an important feature of the esp metric combining these two can help investors find stocks that are ready to beat the consensus at their next report and hopefully surge higher in price too in fact when combining a zacks rank  or better and a positive earnings esp stocks produced a positive surprise  of the time and best of all by using these parameters investors have seen  annual returns on average according to our  year backtest visit the earnings esp center see the full list of stocks to beat earnings research report for hurn all zacks’ analyst reports news for hurn zacks news for hurn other news for hurn should value investors consider huron consulting hurn stock am est zacks avis car reports wider q loss provides  guidance am est zacks hurn what are zacks experts saying now zacks private portfolio services verisk vrsk misses q earnings on muted industry growth am est zacks huron acquires adi strategies assets to expand foothold am est zacks is huron consulting a great stock for value investors am est zacks more zacks news for hurn huron announces second quarter  earnings release and webcast am est business wire life sciences industry veteran joins huron to expand global business pm est business wire skuid hires channels and alliances leader am est pr web financial poise¿ announces evidence rule refresher ep  of the newbie litigator school ii   webinar series available now on demand through west legaledcenter pm est pr web financial poise¿ announces evidence rule refresher ep  of 